:INFO
What the MVP Actually Taught Me Five Years Later
I read The Lean Startup in 2020 when I was three months into a side project that \
was slowly absorbing every weekend I had. The book told me to ship earlier than \
felt comfortable and to measure the thing I was most afraid to measure. I did \
both. The results were clarifying in a way that hurt and helped at the same time. \
Five years on, the project is gone and the lessons are the most useful I have kept.

